title: Vision of the Mothership
desc: A discussion of how Fresno will become a global technology hub.

title: AngularJS
desc: AngularJS is a MV-Whatever pattern framework developed by Google. In this session learn about building Single Page Applications, and super-fast prototyping. We will cover Scope, Two-way Data Binding, Directives, Dependency Injection and more.

title: The World of Raspberry Pi
desc: Raspberry Pi has grown to be one of the most versatile tech in a Tech Geeks utility belt.  Need a Router? Done, Raspberry Pi Router. Need a  Linux box? Done, Raspberry Pi running Debian or Fedora. Need a low energy machine to use as a vpn? Done, Raspberry Pi with VPN. Hungry? Don't eat your Raspberry Pi but get yourself some raspberry pie.

title: Describing the Android Platform
desc: Will give attends a general understanding of the Android development environment, explain the high-level organization and structure of an Android app and introduce how to create and open Android projects.

title: HTML Fundamentals
desc: A light-weight introduction to vanilla HTML. We will begin with a historical overview of this markup language, progress to modern day implementations and syntax, and wrap things up with a look at some developer tools, educational resources, and what languages you should learn next.

title: Google Cloud Platform
desc: No longer are the days where you have to be a developer, system administrator, database administrator, network security engineer, or any of the 100 other tasks it takes just to get a server up and running - just be a developer again. Learn about Google's cloud services that allow you to compute, store, and run applications on Google's proven reliable infrastructure.

title: Intro to Google
desc: A introduction in to Google and Google apps like Gmail,Drive, Chrome, Google extensions on chrome and Google play store.

title: TBD
desc: TBD

title: Linux and Sunshine
desc: Freedom Software. What is Linux. Intro - using Oracle VirtualBox, getting software using apt-get command. Ubuntu.

title: Digital Trends
desc: An open forum discussion exploring trends in the digital age with an emphasis upon tech start-ups and innovation.

title: Intro to Ingress
desc: A look at Google's Ingress game app. How to play, build fields and hack portals.

title: Google Developer Products Overview
desc: A whirlwind tour of what is new with each of Google's developer products. Covering Android, Chrome, Google Cloud Platform, Google+ Platform, Google Drive, Google Maps and YouTube

title: What's New with YouTube
desc: YouTube has matured a lot in the last couple years from a video repository to an integrated horizontal platform for content consumers, content creators, and developers.  We'll look at how recent changes to YouTube have enhanced the capabilities for each of these three groups and explore some practical first steps toward getting the most out of your YouTube experience.

title: The World of DATA
desc: An introduction to relational databases and the role that data plays in society and business today

title: Google Web Toolkit
desc: GWT is a development toolkit for building and optimizing complex browser-based applications. GWT is used by many products at Google, including Google AdWords and Google Wallet. It's open source, completely free, and used by thousands of developers around the world.

title: Intro to Google+
desc: If you think Google Plus is just another social site, you are in for a big surprise. What has been created is, put simply, a phenomenal tool for human communication, and much more. But it takes you to experience it, embrace it and ‘get it’ before this realisation really comes

title: Java Java Java
desc: Will provide some of the basics of the Java Programming Language.

title: Android Application Types & Fundamental Classes
desc: Will cover the fundamental concepts of Activities, Intents, Services, Broadcast Receives and Content Provider, then focus on building a simple app.

title: What's New in Android 4.3
desc: Presentation on What's New in Android from one of the Best Developer Advocates at Google

title: Women in Tech Panel
desc: panel discussion from women working in and around technology.  We hope this will inspire more women to join the tech community, utilize their creative technical expertise, express inspiring vision, and join other active women leaders in creating technologies on Google‘s and other platforms. Men are welcome!

title: Android User Interface
desc: Will cover UI (User Interface) concepts, XML and complete simple app from previous session.
